{"folder":null,"name":"Increased Characteristic","type":"mutation","_id":"1ECoPZDBuuzcjopC","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation, first determine which characteristic is increased through mutation. Roll a D10 and refer to the following chart:</p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Attribute</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>STR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>CON</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>SIZ</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>INT</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>POW</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>DEX</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>CHA</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>STR &amp; SIZ</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9</td>\n<td>Roll twice, using a D8 rather than a D10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>Roll three times, using a D8 rather than a D10</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>Roll a D6 to determine how much the characteristic is altered by:</p>\n<table border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Result</td>\n<td>Increase</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1-3</td>\n<td>+1D6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4-5</td>\n<td>+2D6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>+3D6</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, the characteristic increase is doubled.</p>\n<p>Any bonuses or derived attributes using those characteristics are similarly modified.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699795640188,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Keen Sense","type":"mutation","_id":"7uGoZ67FX2V1bYK4","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>One primary sense (choose) is heightened, raising any corresponding skills by</p>\n<p><strong>Minor</strong> mutation : +20% but see disadvantages below</p>\n<p><strong>Major&nbsp;</strong>mutation: +40% but see disadvantages below</p>\n<p>This mutation may have a physical aspect such as enlarged or unusually shaped sensory organs (eyes, ears, nose, etc.). If using Distinctive Features, any visible mutation should be described.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Following are the senses affected:<br><strong>Hearing</strong>: The minor version doubles the effective range of the Listen skill, and the major version quadruples it. Normal hearing range is 15 meters, assuming no obstacles or interference.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Smell/Taste</strong>: The Sense skill can detect the taste or scent of something a normal human is unable to, such as a tasteless poison.</p>\n<p><strong>Touch</strong>: The Sense skill can detect subtle changes in texture through fingertips or other body parts. The major version allows &ldquo;sight&rdquo; with exposed skin, letting the mutant act in darkness as if in normal daylight, ignoring any penalties from darkness with a successful Sense skill roll.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Vision</strong>: The minor version doubles the effective range of the Spot skill, and the major version quadruples it. It also increases the distance at which the mutant can perform skills at, allowing them to Appraise or Search at any distance within sight.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>This mutation comes with heightened (harmful) sensitivity of the relevant sense.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation , your character must make an Idea roll to avoid being stunned for a round if exposed to an intense form of the sensation (headlights shone on a mutant with keen vision,for example).</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, the Idea roll is Difficult.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699795974737,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Natural Weaponry","type":"mutation","_id":"E1Zej76NLETYUpo3","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant has a type of natural weaponry (claws, teeth, spines, horns, etc.).</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation adds +1D6 damage to Brawl damage. If it is a projectile weapon (spines, projecting acid, etc.) it does 1D6 damage with range equal to the mutant&rsquo;s DEX in meters.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, the damage is +2D6 (2D6 for projectiles, and range is doubled).</p>\n<p>You and your gamemaster should determine whether it&rsquo;s concealable. Use an equivalent weapon for special success type, length, armor points, etc. The&nbsp; weapon&rsquo;s hit points (for parrying purposes) are considered to be their own, with no additional hit points added.</p>\n<p>The mutant can parry with their natural weapon(s), if appropriate, using the Brawl skill. Damage bonuses usually apply. If the natural weapon is used in missile&nbsp; combat, use Throw or Projection to launch it, or a new specialization of the Missile Weapon skill.</p>\n<p>At your gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion, the benefits from this mutation stack with any&nbsp; conferred with the Martial Arts skill.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699796508085,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Colouration","type":"mutation","_id":"EnFfoLCOKVnTW0Gg","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant&rsquo;s skin is an unnatural color or colors, often strikingly so. It may glisten like gold, be tiger-striped, or be one solid color. If normally covered with scales,&nbsp; carapace, fur, hair, or some other substance, that has an unusual and unnatural color.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":true,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699793462349,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Hands","type":"mutation","_id":"GUJrd36tXXCAcd3K","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Minor </strong>version of this mutation provides monkey-like feet; prehensile lips, tongue, or a snout; or a long prehensile tail.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>version provides two such groupings of limbs (prehensile feet and a tail), or an extra set of such organs (two tails, two extra arms, long antennae, etc.).</p>\n<p>Determine if this allows additional actions in a combat round. If using hit locations, the new limb(s) are equivalent to an arm or leg, as appropriate.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699795084129,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Disease Carrier","type":"mutation","_id":"LMLEGCUwoV4lI5cq","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant carries a disease with a potency (POT) of 2D10 but is immune to it. The disease may be promulgated by touch or another mode of transmission (proximity, breath, saliva, blood, etc.), with a range of CON if not touch. Anyone exposed must make a resistance roll of their CON vs. the disease&rsquo;s POT or contracts the disease.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, the POT is 4D10, or is two separate diseases, each with its own POT and vector of transmission.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"dis","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"dis"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699794918485,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Metabolic Weakness","type":"mutation","_id":"QtGumrrPGe9axbGr","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>As with Metabolic Improvement, this represents an unusual metabolic condition, ranging from inconvenient to debilitating, developed with your gamemaster&rsquo;s approval. It could be a shortened lifespan, unusual sleep habits (needs a lot more sleep), a ravenous or unusual appetite (difficult to find foodstuffs), or abnormal growth (perhaps shrinking instead of growing, or aging backwards).</p>\n<p><strong>Minor</strong> version is an inconvenience.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>version is a serious hindrance.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"dis","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"dis"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699796368081,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Natural Armour","type":"mutation","_id":"R71mryIBMVi5Cp6B","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant has an unnaturally tough hide, scales, shell, carapace, or&nbsp;some hardened skin giving protection.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation offers 3-point armor (or 1D3)</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>version is 6-point armor (or 1D3+3)</p>\n<p>Any armor worn is added onto this, though the major mutation requires armor to be&nbsp; very loose or customized. The minor version of the mutation can be disguised, while the major version cannot be easily concealed.</p>\n<p>If random armor values are being used, use 1D3 for the minor mutation, and 1D3+3<br>for the major mutation.</p>\n<p>This natural armor primarily protects against physical damage, though it may also work against additional forms of damage, as determined by the gamemaster.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699796418653,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Group Intelligence","type":"mutation","_id":"SUClKU65RXd3wybp","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This power is rare for humans and picked only with your gamemaster&rsquo;s approval. A mutant with this mutation is either the dominant member of a group of similar linked creatures, or the group itself.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Creatures with group intelligence often live in colonies and share the same mind. The experience of one of the group&rsquo;s creatures is simultaneously experienced by the other members of its colony.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>version, the group intelligence is short distance (CON in meters) and is limited to vague sensations or behavioral imperatives.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>version allows for a strong link (telepathic in nature) allowing full&nbsp; communication over an unlimited distance.</p>\n<p>Often, species with Group Intelligence dwell together and have particular castes specialized for individual roles.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699794983825,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Reduced Sense","type":"mutation","_id":"T4eqWu6kxfSidVok","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This mutation reduces or eliminates one or more senses, affecting any skills linked to those senses.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation, pick one sense. See below for skills linked to each sense. The minor mutation impairs the sense considerably, but it still&nbsp; functions. Any uses of the skill are Difficult.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation removes the sense entirely. Skills linked to that sense are at 0% and cannot be improved unless the mutation is removed. Other senses (and skills) must accommodate and overcome this mutation.<br><br></p>\n<p><strong>Hearing</strong>: This version impacts the Listen skill.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Smell/Taste</strong>: This version impacts the Sense skill in the appropriate context.</p>\n<p><strong>Touch</strong>: This version impacts the Sense skill in the appropriate context.</p>\n<p><strong>Vision</strong>: This version affects the Spot skill.&nbsp;</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"dis","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"dis"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699796920611,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Imitation","type":"mutation","_id":"UTxVxSp7YCZmngAh","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant can imitate a natural trait of an animal species such as web-spinning, wall-crawling, leaping, egg-laying, amphibiousness, etc. (unless the ability is better covered by another mutation). Describe it like a specialty, such as &lsquo;Imitation (Amphibious)&rsquo;. The minor version confers the ability to imitate the trait with a successful Luck roll, or the trait adds +20% as bonus to a relevant skill (or skills). As a major mutation, the mutant is not merely imitating the trait but possesses it, as well as any biological or anatomical structures required to use it. Any relevant skills receive a temporary bonus of +40%, and the applicable characteristic is based directly off the mutant&rsquo;s CON where appropriate.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699795250007,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Adaptability","type":"mutation","_id":"Ux03rZt2uit8jbTe","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this to instantly adjust to a particular extreme condition, chosen when this mutation is selected. Alternately, the mutant can survive the specific condition but does not actually adapt to it (essentially ignoring it).</p>\n<p>Minor mutations are immunity to radiation, can breathe both air and water, can digest metal and/or stone, etc.</p>\n<p>Major mutations include immunity to extreme heat, cold, or radiation; survival in a vacuum; etc. In a resistance roll against the condition, the relevant characteristic is doubled.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":true,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699789582355,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Hybrid","type":"mutation","_id":"VGTARdzrFjJyA9Xn","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Such a mutant is a generic hybrid with the traits of two or more different types of animals. They might have lobster-like claws, a tiger head, or anything else&nbsp; imaginable.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation, the mutant has a few defining elements clearly marking them as a hybrid.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, they are more animal than human, and may find it impossible to blend in amongst humans.</p>\n<p>Generally, characteristics and skills are relatively unaffected, though such a&nbsp; mutant may have claws (1D6 slashing damage), a pointed beak or teeth (1D4 impaling damage).</p>\n<p>At your gamemaster&rsquo;s discretion, the major version of this mutation includes the Natural Weaponry minor mutation (below) at no cost to CON. This can be improved to a major mutation normally.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699795161736,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Metabolic Improvement","type":"mutation","_id":"WW34fwCR8cxzQXoQ","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant has an unusual but advantageous metabolic condition, developed and defined with your gamemaster&rsquo;s approval. It can be a greatly extended lifespan, unusual sleep habits (needs little sleep), a minimal or unusual appetite, abnormal growth (perhaps your character is only a few years old, but has grown at an&nbsp; accelerated rate), altered perceptions, the ability to hibernate, or something else.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation provides an unusual but not significant advantage.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>version of this mutation is a tremendous asset.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699796295112,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Regeneration","type":"mutation","_id":"Wmh1It8ZxnxQaUip","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant heals rapidly.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor</strong> version&nbsp;regains 1 hit point every minute</p>\n<p><strong>Major</strong> version&nbsp;1 hit point each combat round in the powers phase.</p>\n<p>Regeneration cannot bring the mutant back from the dead but heals damage that would normally require hospitalization. Regeneration also heals the effects of any major wound, though the effects only take place once all hit points from the injury have been restored.</p>\n<p>When this mutation is picked, determine one type of injury (fire, acid, drowning, etc.) the mutant cannot heal from.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699797558828,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Sensitivity","type":"mutation","_id":"XzMnhhGq3QKume8h","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant is attuned to a certain item or substance&mdash;animal, vegetable, mineral, energy type, etc.&mdash;which it can detect automatically at a distance. This must be natural to the game setting (it can&rsquo;t be &ldquo;magic&rdquo; in a no-magic setting), and it&nbsp; doesn&rsquo;t work on a specific form of object or being.</p>\n<p>For example, it could be silver, but not silver coins.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation detects the substance within CON in meters</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation the range is CON in miles.</p>\n<p>If more than one example of the substance is in range, make an Idea roll to&nbsp; distinguish aspects such as the intensity/amount/size and its relative distance. If looking for a very specific example, the Idea roll becomes Difficult.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699797667899,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Wings","type":"mutation","_id":"aY5NhocB3NCPXlgt","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This mutation provides functional wings&mdash;batlike, birdlike, insectile, etc.&mdash;or even a gaseous internal organ that makes the mutant bulbous and lighter than air.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation, flight is equal to MOV in meters per combat round, or any slower&nbsp; speed, including hovering. &nbsp;The mutant has a starting Fly skill at DEX&times;2 (plus skill category modifier, if used)</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, the speed is MOV&times;2. &nbsp;The mutant has a starting Fly skill at DEX&times;4 (plus skill category modifier, if used)</p>\n<p>Carrying anything else whileflying depends upon STR, with a maximum of STR in SIZ (or ENC) carried.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699798128418,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Venom","type":"mutation","_id":"h3MdeXwYuwefSBgg","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant manufactures a type of venom within their body and can inject it with sting, bite, spine, or claw, or it may coat their body. Alternately, it might be a gas they exude, projected spittle, or might take effect only if the mutant is bitten. If&nbsp; projected, make a successful Throw or Projection skill roll; if it is dealt hand-to- hand, use Brawl.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation has potency (POT) 2D6 (roll each time the mutation is used)</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation has POT 4D6.</p>\n<p>This poison may cause paralysis, sleep, attribute reduction, blindness, or another&nbsp; effect (gamemaster&rsquo;s approval). A resistance roll determines if the poison has any effect. A ranged venom attack has a range equal to CON in meters.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699798048812,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Allergy","type":"mutation","_id":"hxopZ7cn4K0TK5UF","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This causes hypersensitivity to a particular substance, plant, or animal of a type picked during character creation. Contact with this substance causes an unpleasant and extreme reaction (nausea, weakness, blindness, etc.).</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation, subtract &ndash;20% from all skill ratings while in contact with the allergen, and for 15 minutes afterwards.</p>\n<p><strong>Major</strong> mutation, suffer 1D6 hit points damage when exposed to the allergen once per 15 minutes. Armor does not protect against it, and all skill ratings are at &ndash;40% while exposed and for 15 minutes after.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"dis"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699792862480,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Speech (Mimicry)","type":"mutation","_id":"iyI9NCtoHHoHu1ul","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This mutation grants the ability to communicate verbally. It may be low-grade telepathy, or a simple facility for language learning. The mutant may be able to speak animal languages or might have a knack for human languages. Alternately, they can imitate sounds with great accuracy, including voices, machinery, vehicles, explosions, etc.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation allows imitation of any animal noise; gains a +20% to any Speak Language attempts; and can use vocal mimicry to add a +20% bonus to Disguise attempts. Additionally, the mutant has a starting value of INT&times;2 (plus skill&nbsp; category bonus) in one animal &lsquo;language&rsquo;.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, add +40 to Speak Language and Disguise attempts, and the mutant can imitate a wide variety of mechanical and environmental sounds with facility. They also speak two animal &lsquo;languages&rsquo; at INT&times;2 (plus skill category bonus), and can imitate any other language at INT&times;1 starting skill, assuming they can spend an hour or so in close proximity with someone speaking that language.</p>\n<p>Your gamemaster should determine what animals have a rudimentary &lsquo;language&rsquo; (dolphins, whales, chimpanzees, etc.) and if there is any overlap.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699797761235,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Pain Sensitivity","type":"mutation","_id":"jftrV0yhwGk1a2Ga","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Regardless of their CON characteristic, this mutation gives the mutant a very low tolerance for pain.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation requires a&nbsp; successful Stamina roll to avoid being blinded with agony as if stunned&nbsp;whenever impacted significantly. When taking damage, make a resistance roll of the amount of damage vs. their CON. If the roll fails, the mutant is knocked unconscious for 1D6 combat rounds or until woken up.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation includes that weakness and makes the mutant particularly susceptible to a particular form of attack. Choose a type of damage (fire, edged weapons, gunfire, cold, etc.) that they are particularly vulnerable to. Whenever they take damage from that source, the damage (after armor) is doubled.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"dis","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"dis"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699796627111,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Camoflague","type":"mutation","_id":"mHdapz3s7zhHj99A","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Use this unnatural coloration, exterior form, or ability to change color to hide from enemies or imitate an object or other type of being.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation represents alternate coloration or an unusual skin texture.This provides +20% to Hide.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>version allows changing color and/or skin texture to match the environment, like a chameleon. This provides +40% to Hide</p>\n<p><br>For example, a hairless mutant with stony skin could curl up and resemble a rock or might have bark-like skin and imitate a tree.&nbsp;</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699793364558,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Congenital Disease","type":"mutation","_id":"mp7sT01HPWMdat5q","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant suffers from an incurable and possibly painful non-contagious ailment.&nbsp; It may have hemophilia, deformed bones, cancer, or diminished lung capacity. Such mutants usually have shortened lifespans.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation, one characteristic (usually CON) is reduced by 1D6 points.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, two characteristics (usually CON and another of your choice) are reduced by 1D6 points.</p>\n<p>Any modifiers or derived attributes using those characteristics are similarly modified.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"dis","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"dis"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699793501409,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Structural Improvement","type":"mutation","_id":"pT3pj7Tf8irthsaG","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant has an advantageous evolution in their skeletal structure, whether an exoskeleton (potentially adding to their natural armor), extra legs or heads, larger or smaller body parts, or new parts such as wings, horns, or spines. Work with your gamemaster to determine the nature of the mutation and its effects.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>version, add 2D6 to one affected characteristic, or trade those points to armor points or MOV points on a 1 for 1 basis. POW cannot be altered by this mutation. A successful Disguise roll is required to conceal this mutation.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, roll 4D6 and distribute the points as desired (excluding POW). The major mutation is impossible to conceal, and the mutant may have difficulty finding clothing, armor, or worn equipment.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699797858228,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Pheremone","type":"mutation","_id":"rNAIhlYjxwvUe2Vu","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>The mutant produces complex pheromones that affect the emotions or behavior of other beings. These chemicals may have a distinctive odor or none at all. The effect might be rage, fear, sorrow, nausea, lust, etc.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation, these pheromones elicit one type of emotional or behavioral response (your choice), with a potency (POT) of 2D6 (rolled each time the mutation&nbsp; is used). The targeted creature or creatures must succeed on a resistance roll of their INT vs. the POT of the pheromone or succumb to its effect.</p>\n<p><strong>Major</strong> mutation allows the choice of which emotion or behavior is to be evoked each full turn (5 minutes). The majormutation has an increased potency (POT) of 4D6.</p>\n<p>In either case, the range is the mutant&rsquo;s CON in meters. If personality traits or&nbsp; passions are being used, add +20% (minor) or +40% to a relevant trait if the mutation is successful.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699796696589,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Biped/Quadraped","type":"mutation","_id":"tqAjESaSM2kEBqep","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>Your character&rsquo;s musculature or skeletal structure requires a quadrupedal (four-legged) stance rather than a bipedal (two-legged) one.</p>\n<p><br><strong>Minor </strong>version allows standing upright for brief periods (equal to CON in combat rounds), before reverting to a four-legged stance.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, a successful Agility roll is required for each combat round upright.</p>\n<p>Other characteristics and attributes are unaffected, as is the ability to use some types of equipment, unless affected by the mutation (gamemaster discretion).</p>\n<p>A being normally quadrupedal with this mutation has the musculature and skeletal structure to walk upright, whether all the time or occasionally dropping to&nbsp; quadrupedal stance. For inappropriate creatures (for example, fish or snakes), use Structural Improvement or Structural Weakness instead.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"dis","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"dis"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699793237098,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Structural Weakness","type":"mutation","_id":"vF2b88irqRPoDGV3","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p>This mutation causes a genetic abnormality in the skeletal structure, inconvenient and hindering normal life, whether malformed, disproportioned, or even have&nbsp; additional appendages such as ten extra legs that slow movement. Work with your&nbsp; gamemaster to determine the nature of the mutation and its effects.</p>\n<p><strong>Minor </strong>version of this mutation, subtract 2D6 from one affected characteristic, or use these points to lower MOV on a 1 for 1 basis. POW cannot be reduced. A&nbsp; successful Disguise roll is required to conceal this mutation.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, subtract 4D6 points from STR, DEX, CON, SIZ, or CHA, dividing&nbsp; points as desired. The major mutation is impossible to conceal, and the mutant may&nbsp; have difficulty finding clothing, armor, or worn equipment.</p>\n<p>No characteristic can be reduced to below 1.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"dis","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"dis"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699797946387,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Decreased Characteristics","type":"mutation","_id":"vgT2Ax7M2mWRe7NH","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutation, first determine which characteristic is decreased through mutation. Roll a D10 and refer to the following chart:</p>\n<table style=\"width: 70.935%; height: 293px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 17.4824%;\"><col style=\"width: 82.4168%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Result</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Attribute</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>STR</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>CON</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>SIZ</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>INT</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>POW</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>DEX</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>CHA</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>STR &amp; SIZ</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9</td>\n<td>Roll twice, using a D8 rather than a D10</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10</td>\n<td>Roll three times, using a D8 rather than a D10</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>Roll a D6 to determine how much the characteristic is altered by:<br>Result Reduction</p>\n<table style=\"width: 70.935%; height: 61.9999px;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col style=\"width: 17.4824%;\"><col style=\"width: 82.4168%;\"></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">Result</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">Reduction</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">1-3</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">-1D6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">4-5</td>\n<td style=\"height: 17.3333px;\">-2D6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 10px;\">\n<td style=\"height: 10px;\">6</td>\n<td style=\"height: 10px;\">-3D6</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>No characteristic can be reduced to less than 1, so ignore any reduction beyond 1.</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>mutation, the characteristic reduction is doubled.</p>\n<p>Any bonuses or derived attributes using those characteristics are similarly modified.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"dis","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"dis"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699794626804,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
{"folder":null,"name":"Luminescence","type":"mutation","_id":"x2PfR3WdttXIIKfB","img":"systems/brp/assets/Icons/dna1.svg","system":{"description":"<p><strong>Minor </strong>mutantion can generate a type of light from their body, either faintly glowing or in the form of a beam of light from their eyes or some other body part.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Major </strong>version permits the mutant to emit a harsh beam of light, able to temporarily blind an opponent if it is shone into their eyes with a successful Agility roll: the&nbsp; target can Dodge to avoid the light.</p>\n<p>The light&rsquo;s color, intensity, and any ability to control or alter the light are&nbsp; determined when the mutation is determined. It cannot be overly complex, though potentially could be something like a wisp or ghostlike image. Anything more&nbsp; sophisticated than a small ball of light requires an Idea roll per combat round to manifest and control properly.</p>","gmDescription":"","impact":"adv","minorOnly":false,"minor":true,"category":"adv"},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"brp","systemVersion":"11.0.37","coreVersion":"11.315","createdTime":1699796208477,"modifiedTime":1702582611897,"lastModifiedBy":"NiJh555W408VQRFB"},"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"NiJh555W408VQRFB":3}}
